      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can't advise you to drop down to 2mg of warfarin without consulting your doctor. Warfarin is a blood thinner, and reducing the dosage can increase the risk of blood clots. I recommend you talk to your doctor about your concerns, but in the meantime, I can tell you that 2mg is a relatively low dose, and you'll likely be fine.",
